a2glimpse includes a generated browser bundle in src/a2glimpse-host.html.

That bundle vendors code from Google's A2UI project:

  https://github.com/google/A2UI

A2UI is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
The generated bundle preserves upstream license comments where emitted by the bundler.

a2glimpse itself is a fork of HazAT/glimpse, which is licensed under MIT.

----

a2glimpse bundles the Material Symbols Outlined icon font as
src/MaterialSymbolsOutlined.woff2 so the vendored renderer's icon
component (.g-icon, hardcoded font-family "Material Symbols Outlined")
resolves to glyphs instead of plain ligature keys.

  Source: https://github.com/google/material-design-icons
  Upstream serving: https://fonts.google.com/icons

The Material Symbols font set is licensed under the Apache License,
Version 2.0:

  https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

A copy of the license is available at the URL above. The shipped
woff2 was generated from the single-weight 400 outlined ttf served
by Google Fonts (recompressed via fontTools/Brotli to woff2). No
modifications were made to the glyph set.
